Data Wrangling Assignment #1

Kenneth Larrieu

Import and Tidy

  1. Read the gazetteer data as-is (all columns; no type conversion) into a gaz_raw tibble.
gaz_raw = read_delim("C:/Users/pc/Desktop/gaz_data/CA_Features_20180401.txt", "|", col_types = cols(.default = col_character()))
gaz_raw
  1. Select columns to include in gaz tibble.
gaz = gaz_raw %>% select(FEATURE_ID,
                          FEATURE_NAME,
                          FEATURE_CLASS,
                          STATE_ALPHA,
                          COUNTY_NAME,
                          PRIM_LAT_DEC,
                          PRIM_LONG_DEC,
                          SOURCE_LAT_DEC,
                          SOURCE_LONG_DEC,
                          ELEV_IN_M,
                          MAP_NAME,
                          DATE_CREATED,
                          DATE_EDITED)
gaz
  1. Convert gaz columns to correct type. Convert any placeholders for unknown data to NA
gaz = gaz %>%
  type_convert(col_types = cols(
    FEATURE_ID = col_integer(),
    PRIM_LAT_DEC = col_double(),
    PRIM_LONG_DEC = col_double(),
    SOURCE_LAT_DEC = col_double(),
    SOURCE_LONG_DEC = col_double(),
    ELEV_IN_M = col_integer(),
    DATE_CREATED = col_date(format = "%M/%d/%Y"),
    DATE_EDITED = col_date(format = "%M/%d/%Y")
          ))
gaz = gaz %>%
  mutate(PRIM_LAT_DEC = replace(PRIM_LAT_DEC, PRIM_LAT_DEC == 0, NA)) %>%
  mutate(PRIM_LONG_DEC = replace(PRIM_LONG_DEC, PRIM_LONG_DEC == 0, NA)) %>%
  mutate(SOURCE_LAT_DEC = replace(SOURCE_LAT_DEC, SOURCE_LAT_DEC == 0, NA)) %>%
  mutate(SOURCE_LONG_DEC = replace(SOURCE_LONG_DEC, SOURCE_LONG_DEC == 0, NA))
gaz
  1. Filter out missing primary lat/long, only include places in CA
gaz = gaz %>%
  filter(!is.na(PRIM_LAT_DEC) & !is.na(PRIM_LONG_DEC)) %>%
  filter(STATE_ALPHA == "CA")
gaz
  1. Write out filtered data to CSV
write_delim(gaz, "C:/Users/pc/Desktop/gaz_data/gaz.csv", delim = "|")

Analyze

  1. What is the most-frequently-occuring feature name?
top_feature = gaz %>%
  group_by(FEATURE_NAME) %>%
  summarize(count = n()) %>%
  filter(count == max(count))
top_feature
  1. What is the least-frequently-occuring feature class?
bottomm_class = gaz %>%
  group_by(FEATURE_CLASS) %>%
  summarize(count = n()) %>%
  filter(count == min(count))
bottomm_class
  1. What is the approximate center point of each county?
#center of bounding box for each county
county_centers = gaz %>%
  filter(!is.na(COUNTY_NAME)) %>%
  #remove linear features (features with a source lat/long), only want point features
  filter(is.na(SOURCE_LAT_DEC) | is.na(SOURCE_LONG_DEC)) %>%
  group_by(COUNTY_NAME) %>%
  summarize(min_lat = min(PRIM_LAT_DEC), max_lat = max(PRIM_LAT_DEC),
            min_long = min(PRIM_LONG_DEC), max_long = max(PRIM_LONG_DEC)) %>%
  mutate(center_lat = (min_lat+max_lat)/2, center_long = (min_long+max_long)/2) %>%
  select(COUNTY_NAME, center_lat, center_long)
county_centers
  1. What are the fractions of the total number of features in each county that are natural? man-made?
#determine which features are manmade and natural
class_types = gaz %>%
  group_by(FEATURE_CLASS) %>%
  summarize() %>%
  mutate(type = ifelse(FEATURE_CLASS %in% c("Airport",
                                            "Bridge",
                                            "Building",
                                            "Canal",
                                            "Cemetery",
                                            "Census",
                                            "Church",
                                            "Civil",
                                            "Dam",
                                            "Harbor",
                                            "Hospital",
                                            "Locale",
                                            "Military",
                                            "Mine",
                                            "Oilfield",
                                            "Populated Place",
                                            "Post Office",
                                            "Reservoir",
                                            "School",
                                            "Tower",
                                            "Well"),
                       "manmade", "natural"))
gaz = gaz %>%
  left_join(class_types, by = "FEATURE_CLASS")
#count number of manmade and natural features in each county
types_counts = gaz %>%
  filter(!is.na(COUNTY_NAME)) %>%
  group_by(COUNTY_NAME, type) %>%
  summarize(count = n())
#get fractions
types_counts = types_counts %>%
  mutate(fraction = count/sum(count)) %>%
  select(COUNTY_NAME, type, fraction) %>%
  spread(key = type, value = fraction) %>%
  rename(manmade_fraction = manmade, natural_fraction = natural)
types_counts
